Phase 3:  The Enforcement Mechanism (Anti-Boredom State)The cumulative result: A self-reinforcing loop of passivity.Result: Elites maintain an "Anti-Boredom State" — not through efficiency, but by rendering the populace too distracted and resigned to challenge the wasteful, inefficient control system.
Why It Works: Combines mental suppression (Phase 1) with value inversion (Phase 2) to eliminate creative resistance, ensuring the local error zone (scarcity, bureaucracy) persists unchallenged.

